President Trump addressed a group of business leaders in the State Dining Room, congratulating Steve Schwarzman for organizing the meeting. He mentioned the addition of 227,000 jobs and expressed optimism about the future of the economy. The President also discussed plans for tax and healthcare reform, as well as deregulation. He highlighted the importance of input from the private sector and announced that these meetings would likely be held on a monthly basis. Steve Schwarzman spoke about the purpose of the group and the agenda for the meeting, which included topics such as immigration, regulation, tax and trade, women in the workplace, infrastructure, and education. The President then introduced each member of the group and invited them to share their thoughts.